                    "description": "I teach and co-design a Master's program in applied transdisciplinary research. My role is to grow a high trust community, and facilitate students' personal and professional development. I also mentor teams working on applied research projects in partnership with public organizations or social enterprises. Projects that I've supervised are: \n\n- Sounding Urban Nature - in collaboration with Waag Amsterdam and ARISE, Naturalis: mapping the outdoor acoustic ecology of Amsterdam Science Park and improving it for the benefit of human and other life on campus.\n\n- Nature Intelligence - in collaboration with Institute for Nature education (IVN), Prof. Agnes van den Berg and Dr. Thomas Albers: designing and scientifically validating fieldwork activities that incorporate the concept Nature Intelligence (NQ) in IVN's youth education program.\n\n- Non-profit youth wellbeing app - in collaboration with Anatta Foundation and Positive Mental Health EU Erasmus+.\n\n- Reducing light pollution in Amsterdam - in collaboration with Municipality of Amsterdam.",
